1.00	Laguerre	Edmond Laguerre	Edmond Nicolas Laguerre (April 9, 1834, Bar-le-Duc – August 14, 1886, Bar-le-Duc) was a French mathematician, a member of the Académie française (1885). His main works were in the areas of geometry and complex analysis. He also investigated orthogonal polynomials (see Laguerre polynomials). Laguerre's method is a root-finding algorithm tailored to polynomials, named after him.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Edmond_Laguerre.jpg/220px-Edmond_Laguerre.jpg
